@startuml sq_cli04_parse_cli_arguments
' ============================================================
' Title:     CLI-04 — Parse CLI Arguments
' Boundary:  nasim code agent CLI
' Purpose:   Parse command-line arguments at startup
' Milestone: v0.1
' Version:   1.0.0
' Source:    —
' Review:    docs/audit/audit_2026-06-20_design-chain.md
' ============================================================

actor "Developer" as user
participant "CLI" as cli

box "CLI (cli.py)" #E8F5E9
end box

note over cli
  Scope:          argparse-based argument parsing
  Preconditions:  Script invoked from terminal
  Excludes:       Runtime behavior
  Contexts:       Called once at startup before REPL
  Rollback:       --help -> exit(0); invalid args -> argparse error
  Design:         --model, --server, --no-stream, -c
end note

user -> cli : python run.py [args]
cli -> cli : parse_args()
cli --> user : Namespace(model, server, no_stream, command)

note over cli
  Flow:    sys.argv -> argparse -> Namespace
  State:   No state change (pre-REPL)
  Failure: Invalid args -> argparse error + exit(1)
  Success: Namespace returned to main()
end note

@enduml
